==English==

===Etymology===
From Ancient Greek '''[[κάθεξις]]''' ''(kathexis,''  [[holding]], [[retention]]). Entered English language as a translation for the common everyday German word ''Besetzung'', which in this context means "occupation" in the sense of a position or something being occupied or filled, and not a military occupation of a place or the filling of job positions (although it can also mean either of these in other contexts). In English translations, a Greek word was used to be more scientific.

===Noun===
Freud used the term to describe the tying up of [[libido]] or mental energy on given [[locus]].

